race.description: Rmbl Investments Rising Stars Race Handicap
race.comment: Very even race. ALAA PLENTY (3) has been a work in progress but put the writing on the wall fresh with a fast finishing second. Fitter and has the big claim. Did win maiden this trip when second-up in first campaign and looks a top chance this line-up. ZETALYN (7) is a lightly raced mare with ability who must have had an issue late last year, trialling a couple of times but never starting. Has won the last two jump-outs though this year and looks as though she's ready to fire. Don't underestimate. LYCHEE GREEN TEA (11) is close to a win including a last start placing this journey at Kyneton. Rates highly and should run well. SNAPPY TYCOON (2) was back in winning form with a big win last time. More weight but confidence up and looks like one of the main hopes again. ELLSWORTH (1) was well fancied on debut at Cranbourne and kept coming to score a gritty win. Big weight jump but has upside and can run into the finish again.
